Improve general health and optimize wellness
Strengthen and support the various organ systems, including the immune system, during and after conventional oncology treatment

Incorporate a targeted nutritional and supplement plan based on demonstrated anticancer effects

The founder of Transitional Wellness Center. I am dedicated to the health and wellness of every person who walks through the door.
After serving 25 years in the military as a nurse corps officer (Lt Col Retired) and experiencing my health crisis, I knew it was time to make life-changing decisions.
I recognized that my health issues were not changing like I was told. I decided to use my knowledge of medicine to find other interventions that would help me create a holistic, optimal, and healthy lifestyle.
So, I started rebuilding and restoring my health through nutrient applications and Functional/Integrative Medicine approaches. While on my health journey, I was introduced to the American Academy of Anti-Aging Medicine (A4M) and ultimately completed their Certification/Fellowship Program In Functional and Metabolic Medicine. I then decided to open a business to help others with chronic conditions like myself. I found it a gratifying career, seeing significant improvements in my patient's/client's health through lifestyle changes, natural remedies, exercise, and whole foods.
